  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Construction driver",
  "description": "<p>Job Description<br />1. Transport Materials & Equipment<br />-Safely deliver construction materials, tools, and equipment to and from project sites, warehouses, and suppliers.<br />-Load and unload materials when required.<br />2. Operate Company Vehicles<br />-Drive company vehicles such as lorries, tipper trucks, or vans in compliance with Singapore traffic laws.<br />-Ensure vehicle is used only for authorized work purposes.<br />3. Vehicle Maintenance & Safety<br />-Conduct daily vehicle checks(fuel, oil, brakes,lights,tires).<br />-Report any mechanical issues or accidents promptly.<br />-Keep the vehicle in good working condition.<br />4. Site Support Duties<br />-Assist site supervisors with ad-hoc tasks such as moving materials within site.<br />-Follow site safety rules and attend safety briefings when required.<br />5. Documentation & Records<br />-Maintain delivery records, mileage logs, and fuel usage.<br />-Collect and submit delivery orders(DOs) and related documents.<br />6. Compliance & Safety<br />-Adhere to Workplace Safety and Health(WSH)regulations.<br />-Wear required PPE when entering construction sites.<br />7.Coordination&Communication<br />-Coordinate with site supervisors, storekeepers, and office staff regarding delivery schedule.<br />-Inform management of delays or issues affecting deliveries.<br />8. General Duties<br />-Perform other duties as assigned by management related to transport and site operations.</p><p><strong>Qualifications:</strong></p><ul><li>Valid Singapore Class 3/4 driver’s license with a <strong>minimum of 5 years of lorry driving experience.</strong></li><li>Clean driving record with no major violations.</li><li>Prior experience as a lorry driver, particularly in the transportation or logistics sector, is <strong>mandatory.</strong></li><li>Strong commitment to adhering to schedules, safety regulations, and transportation laws.</li><li>Good physical stamina to handle heavy lifting and cargo movement as required.</li><li>Reliable, punctual, and able to work independently.</li><li>Excellent communication and interpersonal skills to interact with clients and team members.</li><li>Candidates accepting shift working, and overtime working is a plus</li></ul>",
